# @qvac/transcription-whispercpp — Usage Example

Package: `@qvac/transcription-whispercpp` (`packages/qvac-lib-infer-whispercpp`)

Based on the official quickstart at `examples/quickstart.js`.

## Constructor Signature

```js
const TranscriptionWhispercpp = require('@qvac/transcription-whispercpp')

const model = new TranscriptionWhispercpp(
  // First arg: inference setup
  {
    loader,                   // Required — data loader instance (e.g. FakeDL, FilesystemDL, HyperDriveDL)
    modelName,                // Required — model filename (e.g. 'ggml-tiny.bin')
    diskPath,                 // Optional — local directory containing model files
    vadModelName,             // Optional — VAD model filename (falls back to config.vad_model_path)
    logger,                   // Optional — logger instance (default: null)
    exclusiveRun,             // Optional — only one run at a time (default: true)
    // ...args               — extra args forwarded to BaseInference (e.g. opts: { stats: true })
  },
  // Second arg: configuration
  {
    whisperConfig: {
      audio_format: 's16le',  // Audio format: 's16le' or 'f32le'
      language: 'en',         // Language code ('' for auto-detect)
      vad_model_path: './path/to/silero-vad.bin',
      vad_params: {
        threshold: 0.35,
        min_speech_duration_ms: 200,
        min_silence_duration_ms: 150,
        max_speech_duration_s: 30,
        speech_pad_ms: 600,
        samples_overlap: 0.3,
      },
      // Optional whisper params: max_seconds, temperature, suppress_nst, n_threads
    },
    // Optional overrides:
    // path           — explicit model file path (overrides diskPath + modelName)
    // vadModelPath   — explicit VAD model path (overrides vad_model_path in whisperConfig)
    // contextParams  — extra context params passed to C++ addon
    // miscConfig     — e.g. { caption_enabled: false }
    // audio_format   — top-level override for audio format
  }
)
```

## Quickstart Example

```js
const fs = require('bare-fs')
const TranscriptionWhispercpp = require('@qvac/transcription-whispercpp')
const FakeDL = require('./test/mocks/loader.fake.js')

const model = new TranscriptionWhispercpp(
  {
    modelName: 'ggml-tiny.bin',
    loader: new FakeDL({}),
    diskPath: './examples/models',
  },
  {
    whisperConfig: {
      audio_format: 's16le',
      vad_model_path: './examples/models/ggml-silero-v5.1.2.bin',
      vad_params: {
        threshold: 0.35,
        min_speech_duration_ms: 200,
        min_silence_duration_ms: 150,
        max_speech_duration_s: 30,
        speech_pad_ms: 600,
        samples_overlap: 0.3,
      },
      language: '',
    },
  }
)

await model._load()

const audioStream = fs.createReadStream('./examples/samples/sample.raw', {
  highWaterMark: 128000 / 8,
})

const response = await model.run(audioStream)

// Streaming via onUpdate — each update is an array of segment objects
response.onUpdate((segments) => {
  const items = Array.isArray(segments) ? segments : [segments]
  const last = items[items.length - 1]
  if (last?.text) console.log(last.start, '→', last.end, last.text)
})

// Collect all segments via async iteration
const full = []
for await (const output of response.iterate()) {
  const items = Array.isArray(output) ? output : [output]
  full.push(...items)
}

const text = full.map(s => s.text).join(' ').trim()
console.log(text)

await model.destroy()
```

## Response Shape

`model.run(audioStream)` returns a response object with:

- `response.onUpdate(callback)` — called with arrays of segment objects: `{ start, end, text }`
- `response.iterate()` — async iterable yielding segment arrays
- `response.await()` — promise that resolves when transcription completes

## Key Notes

- VAD model is required for transcription; specify via `whisperConfig.vad_model_path` or `vadModelName` constructor arg
- `_load()` downloads weights (if loader supports it) and activates the C++ addon
- `exclusiveRun: true` (default) prevents concurrent transcriptions — throws `JOB_ALREADY_RUNNING`
- Streaming mode available via `model.runStreaming(audioStream)` — requires VAD model
- `model.reload(newConfig)` hot-swaps settings (e.g. language) without destroying the instance
- `model.destroy()` cleans up the native addon; call it to allow clean process exit
